The paper discusses techniques for compiling logic programs into propositional logic, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and logic (cs.LO). The paper also mentions approximation fixpoint theory, which is a mathematical framework used in program analysis and optimization, making cs.PL a likely category as well. Additionally, the paper's mention of autoepistemic logic, default logic, and abstract dialectical frameworks suggests that it may also be relevant to database theory (cs.DB) and computational complexity (cs.CC).
